title: NK cells
extract_protocol_ch1: Venous peripheral blood (60 ml) from a healthy donor was collected in a lithium-heparin BD Vacutainer tube (BD, Franklin Lakes, NJ, USA). Peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) were isolated by Ficoll Paque Plus (GE Healthcare Life Sciences, Uppsala, Sweden) gradient centrifugation and subjected to staining for FACS analysis. The red blood cells in the pellet were lysed with monochloride solution (155 mM NH4Cl, 10 mM KHCO3, 0.1 mM Na2.EDTA.2H2O, pH 7.4) to yield the granulocyte fraction.The PBMCs were incubated with antibodies for 45 minutes at 4°C and sorted in six different populations on the MoFloTM XDP flow cytometer (Beckman Coulter, Brea, CA, USA). RNA was extracted from all seven immune cell types using the MirVana RNA isolation kit (Ambion, Life Technologies, Carlsbad, CA, USA) according to the manufacturer’s instructions.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: sequencing libraries were prepared from 1 µg of total RNA using the TruSeq RNA kit (Illumina) according to the manufacturer’s instructions.
data_processing: FastQC was used for confirmation of the quality of the raw reads
data_processing.1: STAR version 2.1.3 used for reads mapping to the human reference genome (NCBI build 37), allowing for two mismatches and retaining only uniquely mapping reads. The aligner was provided with a file containing junctions from Ensembl GRCh37.65. Reads that corresponded to flag 1796 in the .bam alignment file (flag 1796: read unmapped, not primary alignment, read fail quality check, read is PCR or optical duplicate) were filtered out.
data_processing.2: IntersectBed tool from the BEDTools suite was used to qualified reads that overlapped with exons from known transcripts (as described in Gencode version 14) by no less than 30% of the read's length
data_processing.3: normalized expression RPKM (reads per kilobase per million mapped reads) values were calculated using the formula RPKMg = 109 x (Cg / (N x Lg)) [ Mortazavi A, et al., Nat Methods 2008, 5:621–8.]
data_processing.4: RPKM values for all Gencode version 14 genes were computed at the gene levels obtained for all 7 immune cell types. Gencode version 14 data was used to annotate these regions with protein-coding and long non-coding RNA genes using the IntersectBed tool from BEDTools suite.
data_processing.6: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: a matrix of raw counts; rows are genes, columns are samples
contact_institute: University of Groningen, University Medical Center Groningen
